vysotsky in english events at stanford vysotsky in english facebook twitter email print add to calendar please join us friday february 3rd for a concert by vadim astrakhan a singer guitarist translator who has made it his life's ambition to integrate vladimir vysotsky's work into world culture by translating his songs into english and performing them in a modern musical manner astrakhan has received rave reviews for his translations and his show which is now coming to california for the first time with a show at stanford vladimir vysotsky 1938 1980 remains a tremendous folk legend in russia where he is considered the nation's greatest poet singer songwriter and bard of the 20th century though his work which contained social and political commentary was officially largely ignored by the soviet cultural establishment it has had an immeasurable influence on russian culture to this day the concert is free and open to the public when friday february 3 2012 7 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where bechtel conference center encina hall map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends members tags arts international performance humanities music sponsor creees center for russian east european & eurasian studies contact 725 2563 jscarr stanford edu admission the concert is free and open to the public permalink http events stanford edu events 306 30623 more info last modified january 20 2012
